name: Florentine Bar & Restaurant.

reviews.review_text: Famous for their chicken cafreal. It was really good. we tried the Mixed fried rice, Chicken cafreal & Chicken xacutti. The food tasted good. The quantity was good. The atmosphere is ok. Also we have tried one Pinacolada cocktail, which tasted good. Their service is good, but a bit slow. Parking space is very limited. A small approach road leads to the restaurant.

Worst service. We go there around 10:30 at night, and the waiter on the first floor was complaining it is almost time for closing and asked us why we came at that time. We just ordered chicken cafreal, and four buns. He said they only have two and we agreed. Later another waiter came and throw 2 more buns to the basket like he gave for free. And he ask us to order drinks and we denied. Then he ask to my face, "why you come here just for this. No body comes here just for cafreal, you just wasted your time and our time." and he also commented how fast we finished our food. Worst experience ever in Goa.
A great authentic cozy very goa like ambience...good soul food...mus try and a favorite since years loved by locals is the chicken cafreal...the fry wet bombil and prawns chilly fry was yum...

description:
**Florentine Bar & Restaurant: A Culinary Gem in Corlim**

Nestled within the industrial estate of Corlim, Florentine Bar & Restaurant boasts an impressive rating of 4.2, with over 3,000 patrons singing its praises. Known predominantly for its iconic **chicken cafreal**—a dish that has captivated the hearts of 507 reviewers—this restaurant offers a delightful fusion of authenticity and local flavor, with dishes like **xacuti**, **poi**, and the beloved dessert, **serradura** also making appearances on the menu.

**Ambiance & Design**

Upon entering Florentine, guests are greeted by an authentic Goan vibe that is both cozy and inviting. The restaurant’s décor resonates with traditional elements, creating a warm environment that feels like home to many locals. High ceilings and wooden accents, complemented by soft, ambient lighting, set a relaxed tone perfect for leisurely dining. An appealing selection of music flows gently in the background, further enhancing the mellow atmosphere. Images from eager diners showcase corner tables adorned with colorful tablecloths and plates filled with vibrant dishes that reflect the restaurant's ethos rooted in Goan culture.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

Florentine’s menu prominently features the **chicken cafreal**, which many patrons regard as a must-try dish—juicy chicken marinated to perfection, bursting with a mix of spices that leave a lasting impression. Reviewers have also lauded the **mixed fried rice**, the **prawns chilly fry**, and **fry wet bombil**, with one satisfied customer providing photographic evidence of the delectable plates served. The presentation of dishes is appealing, often artistically garnished, adding a visual component that excites the palate before the first bite is even taken. For those with dietary preferences, the menu offers a variety of options that cater to diverse tastes.

**Customer Experience & Service**

While many have highlighted the outstanding flavors of the food, the service at Florentine seems to be a double-edged sword. Some experiences indicate that the staff may struggle with speed during busy periods, as noted by a customer who encountered a delayed service. Another reviewer shared a rather unfortunate interaction late at night, where they felt unwelcome due to an apparent annoyance from the waitstaff. However, there are also acknowledgments of friendly service that create a sense of belonging, proving that there’s inconsistency on this front. The restaurant does have limited parking, suggesting that it may be wise to arrive early or consider carpooling.

**Popularity & Reviews**

The sentiment surrounding Florentine is largely positive, with a strong local following and countless regulars who appreciate its culinary offerings. Many diners share their love for the restaurant on social media, showcasing snapshots of their meals alongside heartfelt recommendations. While the establishment has its critics, many agree that the delightful dishes—particularly the **chicken cafreal**—outweigh the occasional service hiccups.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

Photos shared by patrons provide a vibrant glimpse into the dining experience at Florentine. Brightly colored plates showcase the enticing **chicken cafreal** and lively **prawns chilly fry**, while the inviting ambiance depicted in these images encapsulates the restaurant's cozy vibe. The layout in some pictures highlights the intimate seating arrangements, perfect for gatherings or casual dinners, making Florentine a worthwhile stop for anyone seeking authentic Goan cuisine.

In conclusion, Florentine Bar & Restaurant stands out as more than just a dining spot; it's a celebration of Goan culture, highlighted by its signature dishes and local charm. Whether you're planning to revisit old favorites or embark on a culinary adventure, this restaurant welcomes all with open arms—provided you arrive at the right time!
